text: AnacranaeMiller NCE (1934) Jour. Fed. Malay States Mus. 17(3): 537. is a genus of grasshoppers in the subfamily Catantopinae and tribe Gereniini. Species can be found in Indo-China, including peninsular Malaysia, where the type species is found.Orthoptera Species File (Version 5.0/5.0: retrieved 5 September 2019) == Species == The Orthoptera Species File. lists: *Anacranae beybienkoi Storozhenko, 2005 *Anacranae gorochovi Storozhenko, 2002 *Anacranae nuda Miller, 1934 \- type species *Anacranae vietnamensis Storozhenko, 2002 == References == == External links == * Category:Acrididae genera Category:Catantopinae Category:Orthoptera of Asia Category:Orthoptera of Indo- China
